# checkrho.dat — Mass Conservation Monitor
# Col1: step          — time step number
# Col2: FTT           — flow-through time
# Col3: rho_target    — target density (always 1.0)
# Col4: rho_avg       — global average density (full precision)
# Col5: rho_drift     — rho_avg - 1.0 (positive = heavier than target)
# Col6: rho_correction— mass correction applied NEXT step (= -rho_drift)
# Col7: SKIP_MC       — 0=mass correction ON, 1=mid-step correction OFF
# NOTE: |Col5| == |Col6| is EXPECTED — both are computed from the same
#       density field. Col6 = -Col5 because the correction exactly
#       compensates the drift. Check Col5 trend for mass conservation.
#
